fn.p:
Notes. HS = high school;
                            IQR = interquartile range;
                            LTL = leukocyte telomere length;
                            M = mean; Mdn = Median;
                            n = number of participants;
                            SD = standard deviation; p-values for comparisons
                            of means were calculated using one-way ANCOVA tests for continuous
                            variables, and chi-squared tests for categorical variables. One-way
                            ANCOVAs were calculated using log-transformed values because variances
                            were not equal between groups. However, reported means and medians are
                            based on raw data.

OR refers to odds ratio based on logistic regression; 95% CI
                                is the 95% confidence interval;
                                IL-6 = Interleukin-6;
                                TNF-α = Tumor necrosis factor-α;
                                CRP = C-reactive protein.
